      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(anthropic): send current claude-cli user-agent on OAuth path",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\nAnthropic OAuth/subscription requests (`sk-ant-oat...`) are sent with a `claude-cli/<version>` user-agent that Anthropic validates against a recency window. OpenClaw hardcoded `claude-cli/2.1.75` in **two** independent places, so OAuth bearer auth fails with `authentication_error: Invalid bearer token` even when the token is valid (issue #94716). Affected surface: the legacy Anthropic SDK provider (`src/llm/providers/anthropic.ts`) and the managed transport (`src/agents/anthropic-transport-stream.ts`).\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\nCollapse the two independently drifting `2.1.75` constants into one `buildClaudeCliUserAgent()` helper (`src/llm/providers/claude-code-user-agent.ts`) and advertise the current `2.1.187` (npm `latest` of `@anthropic-ai/claude-code`).\n\nDeliberate scope / non-goals:\n- **No runtime version resolution or subprocess.** `@anthropic-ai/claude-code` is not an OpenClaw dependency and the standalone CLI is frequently absent, so resolving the version at runtime is unreliable and adds auth-path risk. A single maintained constant is the correct fix here.\n- **No new env surface.** An earlier revision added `OPENCLAW_CLAUDE_CODE_VERSION`; it has been removed to keep the fix narrow and avoid a new operator/auth-provider knob. A future Anthropic recency bump is a one-line edit plus release.\n\n## User Impact\nAnthropic OAuth/subscription (Claude Pro/Max) provider and agent runs that currently fail with `Invalid bearer token` start succeeding, because the advertised `claude-cli` version is within Anthropic's accepted recency window. API-key auth is unaffected.\n\n## Evidence\nValidated on head `8efa69da07a` (rebased on latest `origin/main`):\n\n```\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/llm/providers/claude-code-user-agent.test.ts \\\n    src/llm/providers/anthropic.test.ts src/agents/anthropic-transport-stream.test.ts\n Tests  40 passed + 77 passed\n\n$ pnpm tsgo:core                          # exit 0\n$ node scripts/run-oxlint.mjs <touched>   # exit 0\n$ pnpm check:docs                         # exit 0 (0 broken links, MDX clean)\n```\n\n- Both OAuth header builders now call `buildClaudeCliUserAgent()`; tests assert the UA no longer contains `2.1.75` and equals `claude-cli/${DEFAULT_CLAUDE_CODE_VERSION}`.\n- `2.1.187` verified as the current npm `latest` of `@anthropic-ai/claude-code`.\n\n**Proof limitation (stated plainly):** a fully authenticated before/after against `api.anthropic.com` requires a live Claude subscription OAuth token, which is not included here (no live subscription credential available, and secrets must never be posted). The root-cause failure is already reproduced and documented in #94716; this change is a self-evidently-correct \"stop advertising a version Anthropic rejects\" repair with unit coverage and green CI. A maintainer or subscriber can confirm acceptance with a real OAuth run.\n\nDiff: 7 files, +90/−7 (removed the stubbed fake-token proof script and the env knob from the prior revision).\n\nFixes #94716\n",
        "branch": "fix/anthropic-oauth-user-agent-version",
